    "title": "Bringing Computational Thinking into the Classroom",
    "long_instructions": "<div style=\"background-color: #026C7A; color: #FFFFFF; padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 90%; margin: 20px auto;\">\r\n    \r\n<p style=\"font-size: 44pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center;margin-top: 15px;\">🎉🎉🎉</p><br>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; text-align: center; margin-top: 15px;\">Congratulations!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 10px;text-align: center;\">\r\n        You've finished the second lesson in this professional learning module! <br> Coding Basics with Python is up next! \r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n#### **Reflecting on teaching computational thinking:**\r\n \r\n- #### How did the unplugged maze activity help reinforce computational thinking skills before introducing coding?\r\n- #### How can you integrate computational thinking into other subjects or problem-solving activities in your classroom?\r\n- #### What challenges might students face with computational thinking, and how can unplugged activities support their understanding?\r\n\r\n#### *These questions are just starting points for reflection and discussion—there’s no need to answer all of them. Focus on the ones that resonate most with your teaching experience and goals.*\r\n\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;\">📝 Share in the forum!\r\n</summary>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; padding-bottom:20px;\">\r\n    <p>\r\n\r\n####Participating in the <a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/about-the-cs-ai-foundations-category/40251?u=plteam\" target=\"_blank\">Computer Science and AI Foundations PL Community</a> is optional and not necessary to earn a certificate for this module. However, we encourage you to engage with the broader Computer Science learner community. Please share your response to this reflection in the forum and take the time to read and respond to other educators' posts.\r\n*update link*\r\n### <a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/reflecting-on-your-experience-with-codap/40257?u=plteam\" target=\"_blank\">Direct Link to this Forum Topic</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p></div>\r\n</details>\r\n",
